<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870812-0145 </DOCNO><HL> Litton Gets Automation Order</HL><DD> 08/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LIT </IN><DATELINE> BEVERLY HILLS, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Litton Industries Inc. said its Industrial Automation Systems group was awarded a $17 million contract by San Francisco-based California andamp; Hawaiian Sugar Co. to provide an automated material-handling system at Candamp;H's Crockett, Calif., cane-sugar refinery.    Litton, a defense and electronics concern, said it expects to complete the automated system in 1989. </TEXT></DOC>